page.title: 01Nunkeeling and district
page.content: Apart from the small hamlet of Dunnington which has lost most of its cottages, this is entirely an area of medium, mixed livestock and arable farms, the farmhouses scattered evenly over the area. The land is low lying and flat, although it contains the highest point in Holderness. The only place of interest is the ruined church and graveyard on the site of the ancient Benedictine priory of Nunkeeling. This area is disected by a main road which carries a lot of holiday traffic to the coast.
